        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 11:21PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 1121 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lowell, or 12 miles southwest of Greenville, moving northeast at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Belding around 1125 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Sheridan, Palo,
Hubbardston, McBride, Westville, Butternut, Fenwick, Smyrna, Orleans,
and Sidney.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
